At $450 a kilo Aizakura Wagyu beef is the most ­expensive meat ever sold in Australia.

Aizakura Wagyu beef can trace it’s lineage back to the best beef in Japan which supports its hefty price tag and guarantee of quality.

Called Aizakura H178, one 423kg carcass is now currently the only one available for sale and worth the huge amount of $190,000.

