'This one it hit the mark in every way shape and form,' head butcher Dennis O’Rourke said.

Wagyu breeder David Blackmore and son Ben produce the high quality meat. 

They confirm that the carcass is the progeny of exceptional bloodlines and its origins can be traced back to Japan’s most famous cow - Kikutsuru from the Hyogo Prefecture, home of Kobe beef.

